com.ibm.mqlight.api

Class DestinationAdapter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.mqlight.api.DestinationAdapter<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DestinationListener<T>

    public abstract class DestinationAdapter<T>
extends Object
implements DestinationListener<T>
    An abstract adapter class for receiving destination events. The methods in this class are empty. This class exists as convenience for creating destination listener objects. Extend this class to create a DestinationListener object and override the methods for the events of interest. (If you implement the DestinationListener interface, you have to define all of the methods in it. This abstract class defines null methods for them all, so you can only have to define methods for events you care about.)
